summary.Value: The accounts module handles user accounts and user profiles including login, registration, forgot password and profile editing.

body.Value:
A number of components are available to handle login, registration and password reset.

Links to specific pages showing these components are as follows.

Login, Register, Edit Profile (logged in users only), Forgotton Password

summary.Value: The Demo module contains a number of features used for demonstrating aspects of the Sitecore platform, such as triggering a campaign from external sites or Â information about what the Sitecore Experience Database contains.

body.Value:
The Demo module contains a number of features used for demonstrating aspects of the Sitecore platform, such as triggering a campaign from external sites or  information about what the Sitecore Experience Database contains.

For example, the little information icon shown in the lower right hand side of the screen will open a panel showing information from the Sitecore Experience Database.

The module also allows fake demo pages, for example for initiating scenarios from search engines or social media pages. These pages can also fake referrers, IP adresses and geo location. The pages can be edited in Sitecore but will not affect xDB tracking and analytics.

There are the following examples:

  • Fake Google Page
  • Faking the referrer
  • Faking the IP address
  • Faking Geo location

To test these pages properly, please copy the links, open a private browsing window and initiate the visit by visiting these pages first.

summary.Value: The FAQ module features a handy accordion control to show questions and answers.

body.Value: The corporate or organisational identity of the website is managed by the Identity module. This includes Logos and legal footer information.

summary.Value: The language module contains functionality related to the multi-language support of Habitat.

body.Value: The language module contains functionality related to the multi-language support of Habitat, specifically the language switcher which appears when the site contains multiple languages.

summary.Value: The Maps module allows you to add maps with points to the pages of your website.

body.Value: The Maps module allows you to add maps to the pages of your website. A map can show one or more map points which are stored in a central folder for reuse.

summary.Value: The Media module contains functionality for Carousels, Lightboxes and Videos.

body.Value: The media module contains basic functionality for handling media such as images and videos. Below is a example of the components available.

metadescription.Value: This is the description for the Metadata page. This can be edited in the content editor.

summary.Value: The metadata module covers functionality related to HTMLÂ and SEOÂ metadata.

browsertitle.Value: This is the browser title for the Metadata page

body.Value:
The metadata module covers functionality related to HTML and SEO metadata, including for example the browser page title and global site title.

Open the page source to see the metadata in the <HEAD> for this page

summary.Value: All menus and navigation components reside in the Navigation module.

body.Value:
All menus and navigation components reside in the Navigation module.

This includes:

  • Main navigation
  • Secondary navigation
  • Breadcrumb
  • Link menus (as shown in the footer or header top).

summary.Value: The News module contains news functionality including lists, articles and teasers.

body.Value:
The News module contains features related to news content, i.e. articles and lists.
See the news list here.Â

summary.Value: Page Content contains the functionality and content for basic article style pages, including page title, body text etc.

body.Value:
Page Content contains the functionality and content for basic article style pages. This include:

  • Page title
  • body text
  • Summary
  • Page Image
This page you are currently looking at draws its primary content from the Page Content module.

summary.Value: The Person module contains person-related functionality and content, e.g. employee pages, personal contact info and quotes.

body.Value: The Person module contains person-related functionality and content, e.g. employee pages, personal contact info and quotes.

summary.Value: The visual components for search functionality on the website is contained in the Search module.

body.Value:
The visual components for search functionality on the website is contained in the Search module. This includes:

  • Global search box
  • Search results
  • Search facets

The search module uses the Foundation.Indexing module to execute the actual search.

summary.Value: The social modules contains components and functionality related to social media

body.Value:
The social modules contains components and functionality related to social media such as Facebook, Twitter etc.

Amongst others the module include the OpenGraph metadata and twitter feed components.

summary.Value: John is a highly accomplished executive with extensive financial, operational and global business management experience.

biography.Value:
John is a highly accomplished executive with extensive financial, operational and global business management experience. During 2013, he served as Chief Operating Officer and Chief Financial Officer of Great Kitchenware Inc., a leading network security provider.  He joined Great Kitchenware in April of 2013, and played a key role in recovering the topline and stabilizing operational and financial matters.  Prior to that, he served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Googly Eyes Inc., a leading cloud-based business to business commerce company that was acquired by SAP in October 2012 for $4.3 billion. John joined Googly Eyes in August 2008, and played a significant role on the management team in building a high-growth and highly-profitable recurring global business. He was engaged in all areas of the business and helped contribute to significant growth and an increase in shareholder value, with Ariba's equity market capitalization increasing from approximately $400 million to over $4 billion at the time of the company's sale. 
 
Prior to Googly Eyes, John spent nearly eight years at Johns Livestock, a manufacturer of livestock feeding materials, where he held various senior finance positions, the last one being a global division CFO where he was involved in all aspects of the multi-billion dollar business. He also spent nearly six years in various global finance leadership roles at Toms Petrol and Cafeteria, a large natural resource company.
 
John holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in Economics and Management from Southwest College and a degree from University of Highlands School of Law

biography.Value:
Entrepreneurial-spirited, pioneering technologist with 10+ years of executive-level experience identifying, qualifying, building consensus for, and implementing enabling technologies and enterprise systems that facilitate business processes and strategic objectives. Powerful blend of technology vision and business acumen results in consistent development of powerful business strategies supported by cost-effective, high-performance IT infrastructures and applications.

Broad expertise in IT, network, and telecommunications architecture/infrastructure design, full project life cycle management, client/vendor relationship management, and financial/operational management. Ably manage M&A, reorganization, and process improvement initiatives.
